        "text": "In the early 90's at the College of Architecture and Planning at University of Colorado at Boulder, I spent most of my time in [[The Sundance Lab]].  Mark Gross experimented with a device driver for a Wacom Tablet to see what you could do with three dimensional input (x, y, and pressure).  He gradually built up a diagram recognizer he named Cocktail Napkin.  In the years since then I've decided all designers of all things start first with loosely drawn boxes and lines."
